We recommended, and Management agreed to adhere the provisions of COA Circular 2020-006 on the one-time cleansing of the PPE account of the Municipality, specifically, the following:
Local Chief Executive to –
To temporarily relieve the members of the Inventory Committee to all their regular duties to be able to complete the physical inventory of all PPEs of the LGU as required;
Inventory Committee to –
Conduct a complete physical count of PPE based on the guidelines and procedures provided in COA Circular 2020-006 dated January 31, 2020; and
Ensure that the physical count is recorded/documented in the standard ICF, which shall be used as the basis in the preparation of the RPCPPE after the physical count;
Prepare and submit the RPCPPE covering all the PPEs of the LGU;
Prepare the PIP, and submit the same to the Municipal Mayor to ensure that the conduct of inventory-taking is properly and adequately planned pursuant to COA Circular No. 2020-006;
Submit a copy of the approved PIP to COA at least ten (10) calendar days before the scheduled start of inventory-taking activities;
Prepare a consolidated RPCPPE which will be the basis for the reconciliation of PPE items with the balances appearing in the accounting records, and consequently, investigate discrepancies thereof;
Prepare and update Property records based on the results of the physical inventory and reconciled with accounting records to come up with the reconciled balances of PPE accounts to be considered as the correct balance of the LGU's PPEs;
Strictly implement COA Circular No. 2020-006 in the conduct of inventory of PPE.
Designated MGSO to –
Request the disposal of unserviceable properties by filling-up of the IIRUP and proceed with disposal procedures either thru sale, donation, or destruction following Section 379 of RA 7160 and the Manual on the Disposal of Government Property.
Submit to the Municipal Accountant the duly approved IRUP and disposal documents for recording in the books of accounts, after the completion of the disposal process.
Municipal Accountant to record adjustments after completion of proper reconciliation to establish the correct balances of PPE and other affected accounts, supported with appropriate documents.

